<subSubSection pageId="92" pageNumber="93" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="92.[150,1437,1261,1897]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1621,1645]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">Remarks.</emphasis>
The specific name characterises the flash pattern, where, to the naked eye, the second component of the double flash is not visible (sublustris = gleaming faintly, glimmering). &quot;The 2 peaks are nearly completely separate and the 1st is about twice the intensity of the 2nd&quot; (
<bibRefCitation author="Lloyd, J. E." box="[823,977,1693,1717]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" pagination="991 - 1008" refId="ref127038" refString="Lloyd, J. E. (1973 a) Fireflies of Melanesia: Bioluminescence, Mating Behavior, and Synchronous flashing. Environmental Entomology, 2 (no. 6), 991 - 1008." type="journal article" year="1973">Lloyd, 1973a</bibRefCitation>
). This species was not at first recognized by Lloyd in the field.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="92.[150,1437,1261,1897]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">
<bibRefCitation author="Olivier, E." box="[199,377,1765,1789]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" pagination="316 - 319" refId="ref128819" refString="Olivier, E. (1909 a) Descriptions de Lampyrides nouveaux du Musee Civique de Genes. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, (3 a) IV, 316 - 319." type="journal article" year="1909">Olivier (1909a)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName box="[509,722,1765,1789]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="foveicollis">
<emphasis box="[509,722,1765,1789]" italics="true" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">Luciola foveicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from New 
<collectingCountry box="[867,948,1765,1789]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">Guinea</collectingCountry>
with distinctive pronotal sculpturing and colour pattern similar to this species. However 
<taxonomicName box="[675,881,1801,1825]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="foveicollis">
<emphasis box="[675,881,1801,1825]" italics="true" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">Luciola foveicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(assigned herein to 
<taxonomicName authority="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin, 2013" authorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" authorityYear="2013" box="[1104,1278,1801,1825]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Australoluciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1104,1278,1801,1825]" italics="true" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">Australoluciola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1285,1389,1801,1825]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1285,1389,1801,1825]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and redescribed) lacks the deflexed elytral apex and the pronotal sculpturing of the 
<typeStatus box="[1059,1157,1837,1861]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">holotype</typeStatus>
is not to LB’s eye at all unusual, and quite unlike the distinctive pattern described for 
<emphasis box="[843,959,1873,1897]" italics="true" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ballantyne" authorityYear="1987" box="[843,955,1873,1897]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pteroptyx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sublustris">sublustris</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
